step_original: Common Health Entry Document for Animals (CHED-A) (as set out in Part 2, Section A of Annex II to Commission Implementing Regulation (EU) 2019/1715 (OJ L 261))
step_description: a Common Health Entry Document for Animals (CHED-A)
step_howto_description: The use of Common Health Entry Documents (CHEDs) is mandatory for the entry into the UK of animals and goods. The CHED-A is the Common Health Entry Document for consignments of animals.
